import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'])
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation of electricity in Iowa from 2001 to 2017?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation (MWh)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum').plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net generation of electricity (MWh)')
    ax.set_title('What is the contribution of each energy source to the net generation of electricity in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['net_generation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['net_generation'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['net_generation'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Net Generation of Electricity (MWh)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation of electricity in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    sources = data['source'].unique()
    for source in sources:
        source_data = data[data['source'] == source]
        plt.plot(source_data['year'], source_data['net_generation'], label=source)
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation of electricity for each energy source in Iowa?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation (MWh)')
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
